    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="715"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d715">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9169/4212: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-17">June 17,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received June 26—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–462. For Foreign Economic Administration. Reference Department’s circular
                    airgram May 25, 11:15 a.m.<note n="67" xml:id="d715fn67">Not printed.</note> and
                    Embassy’s telegrams 995, June 8, 2 p.m. and 1037, June 15, 11 a.m.<note n="68"
                        xml:id="d715fn68">Latter not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Country Agency has officially expressed its concurrence to the
                    decentralization rollback to a minimum positive list of commodities which will
                    require import recommendations effective July 1, 1944.</p>
                <p>In regard to the positive list, the Country Agency has asked the Embassy whether
                    the quota to be assigned to Chile of the commodities not included in the
                    positive list will be made known to the Country Agency. The Embassy would
                    appreciate being informed of the procedure to be followed in this respect in
                    order that this information may be transmitted to the Country Agency.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
